        <details>
            <summary>What are dividend stocks?</summary>
            <p>Dividend stocks are shares of companies that distribute a portion of their earnings directly to shareholders on a regular schedule, typically quarterly. These distributions represent a tangible return on investment independent of the stock's price movement. They are often favored by income-seeking investors, such as retirees, because they provide a steady stream of passive income.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
